	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				ok heres the rundown on this quest.  <BR>
Since this is a halfling druid quest<BR>
it will be from that class/race point<BR>
of view.  <BR>
1.get bound to rivervale<BR>
2.head through runneyeye to the western karanas<BR>
plains.  once you get there and see your first <BR>
guard tower take the left path til you get to the <BR>
farmer's fields.  Then wander around the fields<BR>
untill you see a sack.  pick it up and you will<BR>
most likely have a sack of hay.<BR>
3.head on to qeynos.  Once there go to the temple <BR>
of life.  inside along the wall there are merchants<BR>
and paladins.  One of the paladins will give you <BR>
the blessed oil.  Once you get that gate to rivervale.<BR>
4.once done zoning head on down south to the Ferrott.<BR>
One in the ferrott put on your camaflauge and follow<BR>
the left wall till the bridge NOT the lizardman one.<BR>
Once at the bridge go across and follow the shore left.<BR>
you will soon see a lizardman with a wold pet named<BR>
Roror.  Dont worry he's nice.  ask him to bless your hay. <BR>
he will say please give me 66g and the thing you want<BR>
him to curse.  Give him 66g and the hay.  you will get<BR>
the cursed hay.  At that point gate back to rivervale.<BR>
5.Once there go to the druid's guild.  I put 5 points <BR>
into blacksmithing but i heard you can do the task with <BR>
none.  Put the cursed hay and the blessed water into the<BR>
forge.  Hit combine and you will have the Writhing hay.<BR>
6.Give to Shakey.  He will smile at you and give you the <BR>
belt of the river.  <BR>
7.Enjoy the belt and be happy your done.<BR>
I hope this helps everyone.<BR>
P.S. I did this quest at level 9 so low level people<BR>
dont be alarmed to try this kickin quest.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
