				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				     I have completed this hay quest 4 times in last 24 hours, and still have not recieved the Wee Harvester.  I have gotten the Belt of the River 3 times but no Wee Harvester. (the first time I failed to combine the ingredients successfully.)  I was level 16 and 17 every time i turned the hay in, but only got the Belt.  I talked to another druid who claimed he got the Wee Harvester his first attempt, at 19.  I am wondering if you need to be 19+ to get the Wee Harvester.  My smithing skill was 19 when I failed, so I raised it to 40 before trying again.  Now the combination is trivial at 40 (as it was for someone else posted here at 21).<BR>
   Is it possible that we turn the hay into Reebo for the Wee harvester?  or Unerg?  I turn it into Shakey every time and get the belt.<BR>
  Also, the best way i have found to get hay is just to run around the cornfield (in W karana) looking for it.  You can follow Cleet Miller around and wait until he drops some but it is usually much faster to get it off the ground.<BR>
   Roror, the priest in Feerrott, can be tricky to find.  I have always found him in the same area.  As you enter Feerrott from Rathe Mountains, stay close to the right wall (keep wall on right hand).  Roror is usually about 40 feet in from the wall, running back and forth.  If you keep following the wall you will get to a river.  Roror often gets stuck on the rivers edge, right next to the wall.  You can often see other monsters that have gotten stuck there too (neg 1400, pos 1000 maybe?)  Otherwise, Roror just runs in a circuit along the wall (about 30-40 feet off the wall, towards the middle of zone)<BR>
  If anyone might have any idea as to why I keep getting the Belt and not the Wee Harvester please reply.  Thank you.
